	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />There are two (three) great places to test given a multimeter. 
<br />
<br />1- (testable by swapping with another NES) Does the wall transformer work? 
<br />2- Does that power get in? (This is the 5 silver dots that connect the RF modulator to the main PCB, also the 5 pins on the blue connector on the side)
<br />3- Does the voltage regulator work? (This is the black boxy object attached to the RF modulator, labeled 7805 or such)
<br />
<br />After that, however, I'd just give up. Further failures may be simple, but require a lot more preexisting knowledge to find and fix.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


