	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I fixed (or rather, was shown how to fix) an FC clone and an SNES clone, blown 7805 regulators in both cases.  Also the FC clone's capacitor had suffered catastrophic failure (exploded confetti all over the inside of the case).  But those were both caused by reversed-polarity on the power supply, and the NES is protected from that.

		

